## Agent Capabilities

| Capability | How |
|---|---|
| Sync all vault secrets to `.env.secrets` | `make secrets` (needs `SECRETS_API_KEY` in `.env.local`) |
| Push secrets from `.env.secrets` to vault | `./scripts/populate-vault.sh` (reads `.env.secrets`, pushes each to vault API) |
| Get one secret by name (stdout) | `./scripts/vault-get.sh SECRET_NAME` |
| List Vercel env vars | `vercel env ls production` (CLI, project linked at `apps/studio/.vercel/project.json`) |
| Pull Vercel env to local | `make env-pull` â†’ `vercel env pull .env.local --environment=production` |
| Validate all environments | `make env-check` â†’ `scripts/env-check.sh` |
| SSH to Hetzner | `ssh root@204.168.147.100` (key-based auth) |
| Check n8n container env | `ssh root@204.168.147.100 "docker exec paperwork-ops-n8n-1 printenv"` |
| Restart n8n | `ssh root@204.168.147.100 "cd /opt/paperwork-ops && docker compose restart n8n"` |
| Deploy workflows | Merge to main triggers `.github/workflows/deploy-n8n.yaml`, or manual SSH deploy |

## When Adding a New Environment Variable

1. **Store the secret value in the vault first** (`POST /api/secrets`).
2. Run `make secrets` to sync locally.
3. If the app needs it in Docker dev: it's already in `.env.secrets`, picked up automatically.
4. If it's a non-secret Docker default (hostnames, ports): add to `infra/env.dev.defaults` (tracked).
5. Set in Vercel Dashboard (or `vercel env add`) if the app needs it at runtime.
6. If needed by n8n: add to `infra/hetzner/compose.yaml` environment section.
7. If needed on Hetzner: SSH and add to `/opt/paperwork-ops/.env`, then `docker compose restart n8n`.
8. Update `render.yaml` if the service needs it declared.
9. Update this rule's inventory tables.
10. Run `make env-check` to verify everything is consistent.

See `docs/SECRETS.md` for the full developer workflow.

## Known Exceptions

- **Persona routing**: For secrets work, apply this rule (`secrets-ops`) â€” no separate persona required; EA/strategy personas should defer to vault-first steps here.
- `NODE_ENV`: Auto-set by Next.js, never manually configured
- `DATABASE_URL_UNPOOLED`: Auto-provisioned by Vercel/Neon integration alongside `DATABASE_URL`; code checks both as fallback
- Temporal DB credentials (`temporal/temporal`): Hardcoded in compose.yaml, local-only service
